'''Voronica Whitney-Robinson''' is the co-author of the novel ''[[Star Wars Galaxies: The Ruins of Dantooine]]'' and author of the associated short story "[[Pearls in the Sand]]."

Aside from her work as an author, Whitney-Robinson works in [[Wikipedia:Seattle|Seattle, Washington]] as a marine biologist. Prior to this, she spent several years living in [[Wikipedia:Cameroon|Cameroon, Africa]] with the [[Wikipedia:Peace Corps|Peace Corps]],<ref>{{InsiderCite|73|Bookshelf}}</ref> and worked for a time as a veterinary assistant in [[Wikipedia:New Zealand|New Zealand]].<ref name="WOTC" /> Her work in marine biology served as a model for [[Dusque Mistflier]], the main character of ''The Ruins of Dantooine''.<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.swendirect.com/En/archives/whitney_robinson_interview.zip|text=Star Wars en Direct interview - Veronica Whitney-Robinson|date=2004-02-15|work=[https://starwars.direct Star Wars en Direct]|archiveurl=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=btUDB8qOUcY}}</ref>

